### Module 10 — Reads Bookmarks API (Capstone)
### Work through in order. Copy tokens after login.

@base = http://localhost:3000
@accessToken = PASTE_ACCESS_TOKEN_HERE
@refreshToken = PASTE_REFRESH_TOKEN_HERE

# ─── Health check ─────────────────────────────────────────

GET {{base}}/health


# ─── Auth ─────────────────────────────────────────────────

### Register — copy accessToken and refreshToken from response
POST {{base}}/auth/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "James",
  "email": "james@example.com",
  "password": "supersecret123"
}

### Login
POST {{base}}/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "james@example.com",
  "password": "supersecret123"
}

### Who am I?
GET {{base}}/auth/me
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}


# ─── Create bookmarks ─────────────────────────────────────

### Create a bookmark with tags
POST {{base}}/bookmarks
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "title": "TypeScript Handbook",
  "url": "https://www.typescriptlang.org/docs/handbook/",
  "notes": "The official TypeScript documentation. Read chapters 1-5 first.",
  "tags": ["typescript", "documentation", "programming"]
}

### Another bookmark
POST {{base}}/bookmarks
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "title": "Express.js Guide",
  "url": "https://expressjs.com/en/guide/routing.html",
  "notes": "Routing and middleware reference",
  "favourite": true,
  "tags": ["express", "nodejs", "backend"]
}

### One more
POST {{base}}/bookmarks
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "title": "Sequelize Docs",
  "url": "https://sequelize.org/docs/v6/",
  "tags": ["database", "orm", "nodejs"]
}

### Invalid URL → 422
POST {{base}}/bookmarks
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "title": "Bad bookmark",
  "url": "not-a-url"
}


# ─── List and filter ──────────────────────────────────────

### List all (note Cache-Control: private, max-age=30)
GET {{base}}/bookmarks
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}

### Filter by tag
GET {{base}}/bookmarks?tag=typescript
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}

### Filter by favourite
GET {{base}}/bookmarks?favourite=true
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}

### Search
GET {{base}}/bookmarks?q=database
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}

### Paginate
GET {{base}}/bookmarks?page=1&limit=2
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}

### All tags for this user
GET {{base}}/bookmarks/meta/tags
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}


# ─── Read one ─────────────────────────────────────────────

### Get by ID (change ID as needed)
GET {{base}}/bookmarks/1
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}

### Someone else's bookmark → 404 (authorization check)
GET {{base}}/bookmarks/999
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}


# ─── Update ───────────────────────────────────────────────

### Mark as favourite
PATCH {{base}}/bookmarks/1
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{ "favourite": true }

### Update tags (replaces all tags)
PATCH {{base}}/bookmarks/1
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{ "tags": ["typescript", "must-read"] }

### Update notes
PATCH {{base}}/bookmarks/1
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{ "notes": "Updated notes — finished reading chapters 1-3" }


# ─── Delete ───────────────────────────────────────────────

### Delete a bookmark (returns 204)
DELETE {{base}}/bookmarks/3
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}


# ─── Token refresh ────────────────────────────────────────

### Get a new access token using the refresh token
POST {{base}}/auth/refresh
Content-Type: application/json

{ "refreshToken": "{{refreshToken}}" }


# ─── Security demos ───────────────────────────────────────

### No token → 401
GET {{base}}/bookmarks

### Rate limit: run the auth endpoint 11 times to trigger it
POST {{base}}/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{ "email": "wrong@example.com", "password": "wrong" }
